    "body": "F11 always can toggle full screen even in an empty app. Maybe it's provided by OS like Ctrl+W to close the window.\n\nI misunderstood the `accelerator` setting of menu item object. It just shows a text on the menu item, I need to listen and handle the keyboard events by myself. so you can close this issue now.\n\nAccelerators of `MenuItem` cannot work on my Win10 PC except they are same as system shortcuts like `Ctrl+C` for copy.\n\nI need `BrowserWindow` level hotkeys but electron only has global hotkeys. [Other issues about keyboard shortcuts](https://github.com/electron/electron/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue%20shortcuts) covered my question. \n\nNow my solution is :  Add event listener on the page javascript and send message to app by ipc.\n\nPage JS:\n\n```\nwindow.addEventListener('keyup', function (e){\n    if(e.keyCode==123){ //F12\n        ipcRenderer.send('F12');\n    }\n}, false);\n```\n\nApp JS:\n\n```\nipcMain.on('F12', function (event) {\n    let win = BrowserWindow.fromWebContents(event.sender);\n    win.openDevTools();\n});\n```\n"
